// Workspace keybinding recommendations.
// Copy these into your user keybindings (Cmd+K Cmd+S > Open Keyboard Shortcuts JSON):
//
//   { "key": "ctrl+shift+b", "command": "workbench.action.tasks.runTask", "args": "New Blog Post" },
//   { "key": "ctrl+shift+a", "command": "workbench.action.tasks.runTask", "args": "New Analysis Article" },
//   { "key": "ctrl+shift+n", "command": "workbench.action.tasks.runTask", "args": "New Marimo Notebook" },
//   { "key": "ctrl+shift+m", "command": "workbench.action.tasks.runTask", "args": "Open Marimo Editor" }
//
// VS Code does not support workspace-level keybindings, so these must be added
// to your user keybindings.json once. After that:
//
//   Ctrl+Shift+B → New blog post
//   Ctrl+Shift+A → New analysis article (MDX)
//   Ctrl+Shift+N → New Marimo notebook (Python)
//   Ctrl+Shift+M → Open Marimo editor in browser
//
// Alternatively, use the Command Palette (Cmd+Shift+P) > "Tasks: Run Task"
// and pick from the list.
